reviews.text: Oh so good pizza, but oof! expensive. I guess you have to pay handsomely to get the good stuff

Really good pizza. Friendly staff, incredible view and a cool upstairs dining area. My wife and I had the pear pizza and it was amazing. Got some pepperoni slices for the kids and those were also very good. Worth your time if you're visiting Homer!

What more can you say about Finn's? As a Jersey girl who's been in Alaska for more than 30 years, I still miss the pizzas of my youth and cannot abide the pillow-crusted,  kitchen-sink topped pizzas that you get everywhere else. FInn's is the real thing. The crust is perfect, the toppings are limited and high-quality, and guess what? You don't want a bunch of junk on top because the critical elements of a Finn's pizza are already delicious perfection. They're only open in the summer, but at the end of every year I order a few pizzas to stick in the freezer. It's not the same as fresh but it sure is a joy to have Finn's Pizza in the middle of the winter.
Nice semi-outdoor seating above the beach. Super friendly staff that seem to be having a great time.

One of the best pizzas ever!! We visit AK over a month ago, my kids and us still talking about how good was the puzza at Homer! Great service and the place is very charming. Beers were great also. It is a little bit pricy for pizza but totally worth it !!
Definitely, unequivocally and without a doubt  worth it. Make the time and plan ahead to make reservations!

The BEST meal we have had in Homer, really Alaska, in a long time. We were able to get a reservation after a cancellation and just loved it. It’s cozy, delicious, and the service was impeccable. Highly, highly recommend! I wish I could give it more than 5 stars.

Little Mermaid was excellent. We tried to go for dinner on a Friday evening, they were booked through Monday! Reservations recommended for dinner but we were willingly to wait for a table for Sunday lunch. We were not disappointed!! My husband had the wood fired pizza and I had the sole sandwich special both were superb! Highly recommend Little Mermaid!!

Tiny place with great food.  Very enthusiastic service. Pizza was incredibly good. The other entrees were great as well. The blackened Rockfish was tasty. Unfortunately, we had no room for dessert because they looked very good.

Showed up for the home made eclairs and they were delicious. The seating is a hard bench with a tall back and a table that is too high. My wife's feet dangled in the air. The owner (Cathy) did not like my suggestion to put some padding on the bench seats or to lower the tables and gave me attitude about it. Molly the  waitress was really nice.

My favorite!  Mud slides a Must!!!
While lobster salad is a must too. ...the Fresh crabmeat is just as good!!   
On the water, very comfortable outside seating while you wait for a table.
Best place for viewing the ocean while eating your meal. The food is good too.
Its is one of the premier destinations for both tourists and locals.  There is nothing like a frozen mudslide, sitting on Adirondack chairs watching the sun set. Love this place

We went on a weekend evening, not in season (after Labor Day), probably our mistake.  Way too crowded and loud for my liking.  Nice seating outside, but again, difficult to find enough seating for just 4.  There was a place to get your own drinks.... walk up window for people outside, again, long line.  Lovely scenery at sunset.  Once seated inside, our server was pleasant and attentive.  The food was good, but not excellent....certainly not delicious enough to justify the prices.  I think the only 5 star about this establishment was the frozen mudslides and sunset.

Great location if you like boats. Not much of a water view. Mostly summer people, but all very nice. We had good, not exceptional service, she seemed to be double and triple sat, so she did as best as she could. And she was professional and pleasant.  Hostesses could have helped her by spacing out tables. My son had the Lobster Mac n Cheese special, loved it. I had the Halibut special, and was extremely disappointed. They cooked the living hell out of a beautiful piece of fish. It would have been much better just pan seared with olive oil, salt and pepper. It was dry and rubbery. Key Lime pie and chocolate cake were very good. I would probably not go back, that Halibut would have been worth $30 if it was cooked properly, but with all the places on Cape Cod....

The name has changed to Shogun's, but the food is just as good! I have always had delicious food...from the Chinese options to halibut fish & chips! Our family really enjoys this place! And of course, views are amazing and plenty of people watching!

This is now called Shogun's, a much better name, but same menu. Food is ok.  Not spectacular.  I'm a fan of Asian food and it just lacks the freshness and spirit I seek.  But I'm picky. Not on my repeat list with all the other interesting Homer restaurants.  Again, I'm a foodie who operated my own restaurant. Locals like the serving sizes, and this place is popular. Eggrolls taste fresh out of the industry freezer bag.  Soups seem like they come from #10 cans. Staff and service are good.  Always fun to eat anywhere on the Homer Spit too.
Expensive food for the quality and atmosphere.
The name of the restaurant has changed. However the food was pretty good.
Stopped here for lunch. This was one of the best Chinese meals that we've had in our travels. The egg roll was so good that we ordered an extra order.

Unfortunately I didn’t take any photos. The place looks great, very welcoming and the lighting isn’t overwhelming. 
 The food tasted good, reminded me of real home cooking. Like something you’d eat if you went to a pot luck. However nothing but a couple selections really stood out on the buffet from the common stuff. 
 It was the first time in Missouri I’d come across a buffet with frog legs and crayfish. 
 Naturally I thought they’d be the best I’d ever had but they were like the rest of the buffet. 
 They tasted like someone made them at home with no motivation other than to put food on the table. Tasted good. But definitely buffet mass production taste. No love. 
 I got my bill after getting very full on home cooked tasting food that was wonderful. 
 And it was $31.00
One person, two plates of food from the buffet and two sweet teas. 
 One person. 
 I’m sorry to those who may read that and think I’m cheap, I’m just not wealthy. $31 dollars for one person is insane for regular tasting food. Not to mention it was only me...

Went for lunch buffet. It's not bad for the price. A bit limited in selections, but again not so expensive. Mashed potatoes, pork bbq and ground beef patties were great. Kids ate pasta and rice, and they are picky eaters, so that says something. Crab legs normal, same as if you were to buy yourself and put in boiling water. Biscuits a bit dry. They have apple and blackberry cobbler for dessert and can ask waiter for ice cream. Service great.
Great service! Good people! Clean environment. Fresh food. Fish is fantastic! The staff go out of their way to make you happy. The food is priced right, salad bar included. Enjoy!

It was good. They have a full menu plus the option of a buffet. Our group is not a buffet crew, but most of the patrons were. They seated us in the buffet area which meant people constantly moving, getting up and down and it was too active during my meal for me too enjoy too much. Service was good.

The crab legs($10 per pound) were delicious! My mom and I made our way through 2lbs, with a side of delicious okra. My dad had the baby backs with fries and was very pleased with his meal as well. If you don't like seafood I don't suggest the buffet, but the menu has a decent variety of dishes
Very clean and comfortable. Egg rolls are delicious. Beef pho soup is very good but needs more beef. Husband had combo pho and he was pleased with the portion size. We will see this place again.
Yummy curry. One of my favorite spots.
Good food. Was very impressed.
Great Thai food, unexpected heat!  The red curry with salmon was a delicious first-time treat.  Friendly waitress, fast service, clean dining area and restrooms.  Recommend!
Good food, and good service.

A trendy homey local favorite with the organic vegan crowd.  In the past it was well known for great looking fresh smelling cardboard tasting healthy food.  Now the flavors match the appearance and wonderful fresh scents.  A must on your Homer foodie list.

Excellent spinach mushroom soup. We had been referred here so gave it a try for an early lunch. Enjoyed the food but walking into the spot the staff behind the counter were not the friendliest. In such a small town, things like that are noticeable. 5/5 for the soup, 4/5 for the sandwich and 2/5 for the lack of friendly vibes.

Far more than a bakery; go there for lunch! Their fresh baked & stuffed croissants are to die for. 👍
And it's just  short block's walk/drive onto the public beach access point. Love this place!
What a place.  We came here 3 days in a row to eat all kinds of buns.  Make sure to get their previous day's buns at half price.  They are as good as new

Two Sisters had a great small town costal vibe. The bakery is a bit narrow in the entrance but there is quite a bit of seating. I enjoyed my sandwich and enjoyed the atmosphere. The bakery had a large selection of lunch options and baked goods. The cookie I ordered was not as great as I expected, it was a little hard, almost like it had been in the glass case for a few days. But overall great place, ill have to try a different baked good next time.

I took my 3 year old here for a light dinner. I was suprised when we walked in and was asked if we had a reservation. It’s more upscale than you would expect. We had Caesar salads and chicken & shrimp skewers. The food was excellent, so was the service. I can’t wait to eat here again!
Delicious variety of culinary delights. Enjoy the waitstaff that are always wanting to serve your every need. Suggest reservations if you are strapped for time otherwise take your time & enjoy.

I've had two fantastic meals at Cups over the last week. The food was exceptional both nights and the service has been consistently great. I'd highly recommend the Fried Polenta and the Grains and Greens salad on the appetizer menu. Any fish on the menu is also going to be a safe bet but I was impressed with the filet. Order it medium rare and you won't be disappointed!
Best meal in Homer. Really great service and food, I was very impressed. Definitely come here if you need a break from the BS tourist food and want a real, delicious meal. Cute ambience too.
Cafe Cups! Bar None! Have to eat Here! Never met the chefs or owners, best place to eat in Alaska!

Wonderful staff and perfect breakfast this morning. Many great breakfast choices for just about anyone!! They were able to accommodate my special dietary needs. The decor is nice with antique items everywhere!!

This is one of the best restaurants you will find in Homer, Alaska.  The food is delicious, homestyle fare and the service is exceptional.  To me, this is more akin to a fine restaurant than a diner. There are fine works of art by Alaskan artists decorating the wood-paneled walls and many vintage and antique items which are very interesting to look at and bring back memories of calmer times. The seating is very comfortable, with booths which offer some privacy, tables, and some  counter seating on stools for more casual dining.
Breakfast and lunch menu. Nothing too fancy. I had the Turkey club on sourdough, it was very good. The atmosphere was clean, quiet, and quaint.

What a great local place to get a quick breakfast.

Friendly service. The decor is eclectic somewhat reminiscent of a Cracker Barrel restaurant but more quaint and cozy.

Each table has unique salt and pepper shakers. Once we had cows, another time dogs.

There's even a hitching post outside with a saddle on it it you're looking for a photo op.
 
Food was spot on, reasonable prices. Efficient.
Highly recommend.
This place is great breakfast served all day the rest of the menu is great too.
Best bagels I’ve ever had and such a loving atmosphere. You get a warm greeting when you walk  in and a full:happy stomach when you walk out

Hidden gem that deserves its good name. Rarely do we find a spot that hits ranks highly with all my picky eaters, but this one did. Vegan options for my Hippie, fancy options for my Foodie, comfort food for my Homebody, and grilled cheese for . . . my kid who eats grilled cheese. It's a bit of a drive out of town, but since it's Homer, it's worth it.
Excellent place for breakfast or lunch. Great customer service.

Wow! Best bagels I've ever eaten. We liked the Bagel and Lox so much we ate there three times during our weekend. Pastrami Bagel sandwich was awesome as well. Sadly all bagels from here on out will pale in comparison. You can tell this place is at the top of its game.
Bacon egg and cheese on a sesame seed bagel was so delicious i had to order a second one right after i was done.

reviews.text: Great crew staff will point u in the right direction.
